Job Description:
Mandatory Skill-set
Degree or Diploma in Software Engineering, Computer Engineering, or equivalent;
Overall 8 to 12 years of working experience in IT industry with team leading experience;
Hands-on experience in 24/7 mission-critical enterprise environments and associated IT systems;
Proven track record in re-engineering and optimizing critical and complex batch jobs to ensure high availability, cost efficiency, and minimal impact on the hosting application systems;
Lead technical teams, cultivating a collaborative environment that fosters growth and development;
In depth understanding of Batch Job Platforms like BMC, control M / VisualCron;
Exposure to application development with an understanding of common programming languages such as Java / .NET;
Proficient in navigating dynamic, fast-paced environments with multiple interdependent teams;
Must have good communication skills and adept at collaborative work within a professional environment;
Desired Skill-set
Exposure to ITIL (Incident, Problem & Change management).
Responsibilities
Be a Subject Matter Expert (SME) and Administrator for Batch Job Platforms providing solutions for running and optimizing the job workloads;
Schedule, monitor, and maintain batch jobs using enterprise scheduling tools (e.g.,BMC, Control-M, VisualCron, Autosys etc.).
Develop and implement job streams and workflows to ensure timely and accurate processing of data;
Monitor batch job executions, ensuring they complete successfully and within defined SLAs;
Troubleshoot and resolve batch job failures, collaborating with application developers and system administrators as needed
Analyze job performance and recommend improvements to optimize processing times and resource utilization;
Develop and Implement Policies for Standard Batch Job Execution and Monitoring, Demonstrating Proficiency in Relevant Technologies and Frameworks;
Stay current with technological advancements and recommend updates or new tools to improve batch processing operations.

Mandatory Skill-set
Degree in Computer Science, Information Systems, Data Science or equivalent;
Proficiency in analyzing large, complex data sets to identify trends, patterns, and actionable insights;
Experience with statistical analysis and data visualization tools (e.g., Power BI, Tableau, Excel);
Knowledge of ETL processes and data transformation techniques;
Ability to align data analysis with business objectives and communicate complex data insights to non-technical stakeholders;
Experience implementing and maintaining data quality standards and improving data accuracy and reliability;
Proficient in SQL for querying and manipulating data in various databases (e.g., Oracle, SQL Server, MySQL, PostgreSQL);
Ability to lead discussions, negotiate solutions, and drive consensus across multiple stakeholders;
Strong written and verbal communication skills.
Desired Skill-set
Experience with agile methodologies or similar frameworks for managing project tasks and deliverables;
Prior experience with banking clients.
Responsibilities
Analyze and assess various data sources to determine their suitability and alignment with the business’s cost allocation requirements across the enterprise;
Identify trends and patterns within complex data sets and collaborate with business and finance stakeholders to validate findings and obtain necessary approvals;
Work closely with upstream data providers and other stakeholders to identify and resolve data issues, ensuring data quality and accuracy;
Define and implement ETL processes and transformation rules to ensure data aligns with the organization’s data standards and requirements;
Assist users and business unit controllers in translating business data requirements into clear, actionable deliverables, ensuring data solutions meet their needs;
Collaborate with business analysts, subject matter experts, and technology leads to conduct current state analyses, suggest process improvements, and address data quality issues;
Establish and enforce data governance policies and practices related to data quality metrics, metadata management, data lineage, access control, and business definitions;
Facilitate stakeholder working groups to drive discussions that result in targeted business outcomes, ensuring alignment across teams;
Maintain clear and consistent communication with all stakeholders, ensuring effective coordination and the timely completion of tasks and activities.
